      "content": "It's not uncommon for asthma symptoms to worsen with age, but feeling winded from minimal activities could indicate a need for better asthma management. I recommend you to take your inhaler as prescribed and consider a quick puff before you walk to the kitchen. Also, a good night's sleep and a balanced diet can improve your respiratory function. If you continue to experience shortness of breath, it's always a good idea to consult your doctor.",
